.TH PALETTE-THEMING 1 "2026-03-11" "sway dotfiles" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
palette-theming \- live color palette theming system for sway
.SH DESCRIPTION
The Palette Theming system provides coordinated color palette switching
across sway window borders, the foot terminal, waybar, rofi, wofi, and
the eww widget toolkit. GTK, Qt/Kvantum, icon, and cursor themes are
applied simultaneously via
.IR 90-enable-theme.conf .
.PP
The system consists of seven scripts and twelve palette theme definitions
under
.IR ~/.config/sway/themes/ .
Each theme carries two files: a sway
.I theme.conf
(color variables and
.B client.*
window decoration rules) and a
.I foot-theme.ini
(16-color terminal palette for the foot terminal emulator).
.PP
On every theme switch, the orchestrator
.B theme-selector.sh
(1) symlinks the chosen
.I theme.conf
as the active sway theme, (2) copies the
.I foot-theme.ini
to the runtime location read by foot, (3) pushes the new palette to all
running terminal instances via OSC escape sequences (no restart needed),
(4) syncs the icon theme to
.IR qt6ct.conf ,
(5) updates Papirus folder colors for catppuccin themes,
(6) reloads sway so window decorations and GTK/Qt/Kvantum themes update,
and (7) regenerates the waybar CSS, rofi color variables, wofi stylesheet,
and eww SCSS, then signals waybar.
.PP
A secondary script
.BR theme-toggle.sh
provides automatic light/dark switching based on local sunrise and sunset
times obtained from
.BR geoip.sh .
.SH KEYBINDINGS
.TP
.B $mod+t
Open the theme picker (wofi dmenu). Calls
.IR theme-selector.sh\ menu .
.TP
.B Waybar custom/theme (left-click)
Manually toggle light \[<>] dark palette. Calls
.IR theme-toggle.sh\ toggle .
.TP
.B Waybar custom/theme (right-click)
Enable or disable automatic solar-time switching. Calls
.IR theme-toggle.sh\ auto-toggle .
.SH FILES
.SS Core scripts
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/theme-selector.sh
Main orchestrator. Implements
.B menu
(wofi picker + apply) and
.B status
(waybar JSON icon) modes.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/theme-apply-foot.sh
Parses a foot-theme.ini and writes OSC 10/11/4;N escape sequences to
all writable
.I /dev/pts/*
PTY slave devices, applying colors to running terminals in real time.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/theme-waybar.sh
Reads the active
.I theme.conf
symlink, resolves
.BR $background-color ,
.BR $text-color ,
and
.B $accent-color
(one level of variable indirection supported), and generates
.IR ~/.config/waybar/theme.css .
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/theme-rofi.sh
Reads the active
.I theme.conf
symlink, resolves
.BR $background-color ,
.BR $text-color ,
.BR $accent-color ,
and
.B $selection-color
(one level of variable indirection supported), and generates
.IR ~/.config/rofi/cachyos.rasi .
Called by
.I theme-selector.sh
on every theme switch and by
.I $update_rofi_theme
on every sway reload.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/theme-wofi.sh
Reads the active
.I theme.conf
symlink, resolves
.BR $background-color ,
.BR $text-color ,
.BR $accent-color ,
and
.B $selection-color
(one level of variable indirection supported), and generates
.IR ~/.config/wofi/style.css .
Called by
.I theme-selector.sh
on every theme switch.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/theme-eww.sh
Reads the active
.I theme.conf
symlink, resolves
.BR $background-color ,
.BR $text-color ,
.BR $accent-color ,
and
.B $selection-color
(one level of variable indirection supported), and generates
.IR ~/.config/eww/styles/theme.scss .
eww watches its SCSS files and reloads automatically \[em] no eww
restart is needed. Called by
.I theme-selector.sh
on every theme switch.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/theme-toggle.sh
Light/dark palette toggle based on solar time. Uses geoip.sh for
sunrise/sunset. Stashes the inactive variant as
.I theme.dark.conf_
/
.I theme.light.conf_
and swaps on request or automatically.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/wob.sh
Wrapper script for the
.BR wob (1)
on-screen bar (volume/brightness indicator). Receives the active
.B $accent-color
and
.B $background-color
as arguments (injected by sway via
.IR $onscreen_bar )
and writes
.IR ~/.config/wob.ini ,
then spawns or reuses a running wob instance. Colors are therefore
always in sync with the active palette without an explicit theme-switch
step.
.SS Theme picker
.TP
.I ~/.config/wofi/config
Configures the wofi dmenu instance that renders the theme selection list
on
.BR $mod+t .
Sets geometry (35\[tmu]45%, centered), dmenu mode, case-insensitive
filtering, and icon display.
.TP
.I ~/.config/wofi/style.css
GTK CSS stylesheet for the theme picker window rendered by
.BR wofi (1).
.B Auto-generated
by
.I theme-wofi.sh
on every theme switch. Styles the border, background, entry list, and
selection highlight using the active palette colors.
.SS Theme data (one pair per theme)
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/themes/<name>/theme.conf
Color variable definitions (
.B $color0
\[en]
.BR $color15 ,
or Catppuccin-named variables),
.BR $background-color ,
.BR $text-color ,
.BR $accent-color ,
.BR $selection-color ,
.BR $gtk-theme ,
.BR $icon-theme ,
.BR $cursor-theme ,
.BR $kvantum-theme ,
.BR $gui-font ,
.BR $term-font ,
and
.B $gtk-color-scheme
) and sway
.B client.*
window decoration rules.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/themes/<name>/foot-theme.ini
Terminal palette in foot config format. Includes
.I ~/.config/sway/templates/foot.ini
for shared non-color settings.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/themes/<name>/packages
Plain-text list of AUR/pacman packages required by this theme (GTK
theme, icon theme, cursor theme, Kvantum theme, fonts). Used as
documentation; not parsed by any script.
.PP
Available themes:
catppuccin-frappe, catppuccin-latte, catppuccin-macchiato, catppuccin-mocha,
dracula, gruvbox-dark, matcha-blue, matcha-green, matcha-leaf, matcha-red,
nordic-bluish-accent, tokyo-night.
.SS Active theme (runtime \(em do not edit or track in git)
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/definitions.d/theme.conf
Symlink pointing to the selected theme's
.IR theme.conf .
Recreated by
.I theme-selector.sh
on each switch.
.TP
.I ~/.config/foot/foot-theme.ini
File copy (not a symlink) of the selected theme's
.IR foot-theme.ini .
Must be a copy so that foot can
.B include=
it without runtime-vs-source ambiguity.
Updated by
.I theme-selector.sh
on each switch.
.TP
.I ~/.config/waybar/theme.css
Auto-generated CSS with
.B @define-color
rules. Overwritten by
.I theme-waybar.sh
on each switch.
.TP
.I ~/.config/rofi/cachyos.rasi
Auto-generated rofi color variables. Defines
.BR background-color ,
.BR text-color ,
.BR accent-color ,
and
.B selected-bg
for rofi. Imported by
.I ~/.config/rofi/config.rasi
via
.BR "@import \(dqcachyos\(dq" .
Overwritten by
.I theme-rofi.sh
on each switch.
.TP
.I ~/.config/wofi/style.css
Auto-generated GTK CSS for the wofi theme picker. Overwritten by
.I theme-wofi.sh
on each switch.
.TP
.I ~/.config/eww/styles/theme.scss
Auto-generated SCSS defining
.BR $theme-bg ,
.BR $theme-fg ,
.BR $theme-accent ,
and
.B $theme-selection
variables. Overwritten by
.I theme-eww.sh
on each switch. eww reloads it automatically via filesystem watch.
.TP
.I ~/.config/wob.ini
Auto-generated wob configuration. Written by
.I wob.sh
each time wob is launched or refreshed, using colors passed via
.IR $onscreen_bar .
.SS Templates
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/templates/foot.ini
Shared foot settings (font, scrollback, key bindings, cursor, bell).
Included by every
.I foot-theme.ini
via
.BR include= .
.SS Configuration references (files that use but do not belong to this system)
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/config
Includes
.I ~/.config/sway/definitions.d/theme.conf
to inject color variables into the sway config tree.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/modes/default
Binds
.B $mod+t
to
.IR theme-selector.sh\ menu .
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/config.d/90-enable-theme.conf
Applied on every sway reload. Calls
.I enable-gtk-theme.sh
to apply the GTK theme to GTK3/4 apps, sets
.BR gsettings (1)
for icon theme, cursor theme, fonts, and color scheme, and calls
.B "kvantummanager --set"
to activate the Kvantum theme for Qt apps.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/config.d/01-definitions.conf
Defines the
.B $onscreen_bar
sway variable as
.IR "wob.sh \(dq$accent-color\(dq \(dq$background-color\(dq" ,
so every keybinding that pipes a value to wob automatically uses
the active palette.
.TP
.I ~/.config/qt6ct/qt6ct.conf
Qt6 platform theme configuration. The
.B icon_theme
key is updated on every theme switch by
.I theme-selector.sh
to match
.B $icon-theme
from the active theme, so Qt6 apps use the correct icon set.
.TP
.I ~/.config/foot/foot.ini
Includes
.I foot-theme.ini
and sets
.B initial-color-theme=dark
so new windows open with
.BR [colors-dark] .
.TP
.I ~/.config/waybar/style.css
Imports
.I theme.css
via
.BR "@import \(dqtheme.css\(dq;" .
.TP
.I ~/.config/waybar/config.jsonc
Defines the
.B custom/theme
module which calls
.I theme-toggle.sh
for status, click, and right-click actions.
.SH PROGRAMS
.BR wofi (1),
.BR swaymsg (1),
.BR pkill (1),
.BR awk (1),
.BR grep (1),
.BR sed (1),
.BR foot (1),
.BR jq (1),
.BR mv (1),
.BR gsettings (1),
.BR kvantummanager (1),
.BR papirus-folders (1),
.BR wob (1)
.SH FLOW
.SS Theme switch (super+t)
.nr step 1 1
.IP \n[step]. 3
User presses
.B $mod+t
\[->]
.I theme-selector.sh menu
launches a wofi dmenu listing all directories under
.I ~/.config/sway/themes/
.IP \n+[step].
User selects a theme \[->]
.I apply_theme()
is called
.IP \n+[step].
.I theme.conf
for the chosen theme is symlinked to
.I ~/.config/sway/definitions.d/theme.conf
.IP \n+[step].
.I foot-theme.ini
is copied (not symlinked) to
.I ~/.config/foot/foot-theme.ini
.IP \n+[step].
.I theme-apply-foot.sh
writes OSC payloads to all
.I /dev/pts/*
\[->] running foot instances change colors instantly
.IP \n+[step].
.B $icon-theme
is read from
.I theme.conf
and written to
.B icon_theme
in
.I ~/.config/qt6ct/qt6ct.conf
\[->] Qt6 apps use the correct icon set on next launch
.IP \n+[step].
For catppuccin themes:
.B papirus-folders
is called with the matching
.I cat-<flavor>-blue
color and Papirus-Dark or Papirus-Light \[->] Papirus folder icons
update immediately
.IP \n+[step].
.BR "swaymsg reload"
\[->] sway re-reads theme.conf \[->] window borders update and
.I 90-enable-theme.conf
applies GTK theme, icon theme, cursor theme, fonts, color scheme,
and Kvantum theme
.IP \n+[step].
.IR theme-waybar.sh ,
.IR theme-rofi.sh ,
.IR theme-wofi.sh ,
and
.I theme-eww.sh
regenerate their respective output files
.IP \n+[step].
.B "pkill -SIGUSR2 waybar"
reloads waybar CSS \[->]
.B "pkill -RTMIN+17 waybar"
refreshes the theme icon
.SS New terminal window (any time)
Foot reads
.I ~/.config/foot/foot.ini
\[->] includes
.I foot-theme.ini
\[->] loads
.B [colors-dark]
\[->] opens with the palette that was active when the last theme switch happened.
.SS Wob on-screen bar (volume/brightness)
Any keybinding that triggers wob calls
.I $onscreen_bar
(defined in
.IR 01-definitions.conf )
which expands to
.IR "wob.sh \(dq$accent-color\(dq \(dq$background-color\(dq <value>" .
.I wob.sh
generates
.I ~/.config/wob.ini
with the current accent/background colors, then pipes the value to the
running wob instance (or spawns a new one). No explicit theme-switch
step is needed \[em] wob always inherits the live sway variables.
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGUSR2
Sent to
.BR waybar (1)
to trigger a CSS stylesheet reload.
.TP
.B SIGRTMIN+17
Sent to
.BR waybar (1)
to refresh the
.B custom/theme
module output (icon and tooltip).
.SH WAYBAR INTEGRATION
The
.B custom/theme
module in
.I ~/.config/waybar/config.jsonc
shows a moon/sun icon and the active theme name. It calls
.IR theme-toggle.sh\ status
periodically, and on left/right click calls
.I toggle
and
.I auto-toggle
respectively.
.PP
All waybar module colors derive from the CSS variables defined in
.I ~/.config/waybar/theme.css
(imported by
.IR style.css ).
The three primary variables are:
.BR @theme_base_color ,
.BR @theme_text_color ,
and
.BR @theme_selected_bg_color .
.SH NOTES
.IP \[bu] 2
Live terminal recoloring works because writing to a
.I /dev/pts/N
slave device sends data to the terminal master's read buffer.
Foot (the master) processes OSC sequences as program output and updates
its palette without a restart.
.IP \[bu]
Foot does not support a
.B SIGHUP
config reload (the developer explicitly rejected it), so the OSC
mechanism is the only way to recolor running instances.
.IP \[bu]
GTK apps pick up theme changes instantly via the
.BR gsettings (1)
bus (GSettings notification). GTK4/libadwaita apps may require a
restart in some cases.
.IP \[bu]
Qt/Kvantum apps require a restart to pick up Kvantum theme changes.
.B kvantummanager --set
updates the active theme on disk; running Qt processes do not reload it.
Qt6 icon theme changes (via
.IR qt6ct.conf )
also require a restart.
.IP \[bu]
Cursor theme changes apply to newly launched apps immediately.
Existing windows may not update until restarted.
.IP \[bu]
GTK, Qt, and Kvantum theme application is performed by
.I 90-enable-theme.conf
(via
.IR enable-gtk-theme.sh )
on every sway reload. That system reads
.BR $gtk-theme ,
.BR $icon-theme ,
.BR $cursor-theme ,
and
.B $kvantum-theme
variables from
.I theme.conf
but its operation is independent of the palette scripts documented here.
.IP \[bu]
The matcha-* themes and dracula share the same Base16 Seti UI base
palette. Their distinction comes from the accent color and, for dracula,
the Dracula purple (#bd93f9) in the ANSI blue slot (regular4/bright4).
.IP \[bu]
Catppuccin themes use named palette variables (rosewater, flamingo,
base, surface1, etc.) instead of $color0\[en]$color15. The four
catppuccin flavors (frappe, latte, macchiato, mocha) share the same
GTK, cursor, and Kvantum package families, differing only in palette
values. Latte is the only light theme; it uses
.B prefer-light
and
.IR Papirus-Light .
.SH SEE ALSO
